The paper deals with the problem of learning to decompose spatial tasks into segments, which is a common problem in computer vision and robotics. The paper proposes a novel approach to solve this problem using neural parsers and deterministic differentiable imitation learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also introduces a novel policy gradient update, which is relevant to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The problem of decomposing objects into segments is also relevant to the sub-categories cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
